@startuml
' ==========================================================
' Diagramme de classes participantes — Cas d’utilisation : Authentification
' Objectif : montrer les classes impliquées dans la connexion + sessions JWT (cookies)
' Alignement : `backend/routes/api/authRoutes.js`, `backend/services/authService.js`, `backend/middleware/auth.js`
' ==========================================================

title Diagramme de classes participantes — UC "Authentification"
left to right direction
skinparam dpi 160
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam linetype ortho
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam wrapWidth 220

class AuthRoutes <<controller>> {
  +POST /api/auth/login()
  +POST /api/auth/logout()
  +POST /api/auth/refresh()
  +GET /api/auth/me()
}

class AuthService <<service>> {
  +loginUser({ email, password, device? })
  +logoutUser(userId, refreshPlain)
  +refreshSession(refreshPlain, device?)
}

class AuthMiddleware <<middleware>> {
  +requireAuth()
  +optionalAuth()
  +readRefreshToken()
}

class User <<model>> {
  +email
  +passwordHash
  +role
  +isActive
  +refreshTokens[]
}

class RefreshToken <<embedded>> {
  +tokenHash
  +expiresAt
  +device
}

class CookieOptions <<util>> {
  +accessTokenCookieOptions()
  +refreshTokenCookieOptions()
}

AuthRoutes ..> AuthService
AuthRoutes ..> AuthMiddleware
AuthService ..> User
User *-- "0..*" RefreshToken
AuthRoutes ..> CookieOptions

note bottom of CookieOptions
  Cookies : access_token, refresh_token\n
  Option `sameSite` = `lax` ; option `secure` activée uniquement en production.
end note

@enduml

